<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-12-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-12-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="677" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d677">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Olney</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Terrell</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-12-13"><hi rend="italic">December 13,
                                    1895</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Referring to last paragraph your 685, admiral has been telegraphed to
                            cooperate heartily with you and enforce all writs issued by you to
                            prevent any entry into Turkey of naturalized citizens as armed
                            revolutionists under provisions of section cited.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Olney.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>